   {
      "body" : "We've tracked this issue down to the sdk used to build qt. When built with >= 10.8 sdk, qt uses new apis to discover fonts, rather than the old unreliable methods. For master, we should bump up to a newer SDK. For 0.10, we have a few options.\r\n\r\nSome background info on SDKs: https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/5582#issuecomment-68463725\r\n\r\nOptions:\r\n- Remove the thin-space stuff for 0.10, possibly only for osx 10.10. That wouldn't address #5165.\r\n- Build 0.10 against 10.8\r\n- Track down the font loading failure and attempt to insert a work-around like 292cc072f3bada256bc6af9970512eb9dec8d93a\r\n\r\nI'd prefer to do the last one, if it's possible. Looking into it now.",
      "created_at" : "2015-01-14T19:53:58Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/5657#issuecomment-69979978",
